Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/migrating/app-router-migration.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to define page metadata, such as title and description, using the `metadata` export in `app/layout.tsx` or `app/layout.js`. This declarative approach replaces traditional `<head>` tag management for SEO purposes within the Next.js App Router, automatically updating the document's head.

```tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next'

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Home',
  description: 'Welcome to Next.js',
}
```

```jsx
