  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <div id="root">{children}</div>
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

--------------------------------

### Define Static Metadata with Next.js `metadata` Object

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/generate-metadata.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to define static metadata by exporting a `metadata` object from a `layout.js` or `page.js` file in a Next.js application. It sets basic SEO properties like title and description. This approach is suitable for metadata that does not depend on dynamic data and will be included in the page’s initial HTML.

```typescript
import type { Metadata } from 'next'

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: '...', 
  description: '...', 
}

export default function Page() {}
```

```javascript
export const metadata = {
  title: '...', 
  description: '...', 
}

export default function Page() {}
```

--------------------------------

### Migrate Next.js `next/head` for Metadata to App Directory SEO

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/migrating/app-router-migration.mdx

This example demonstrates how to transition from managing HTML `<head>` elements using the `next/head` React component in the `pages` directory to the new built-in SEO and metadata support provided by the `app` directory. It includes both TypeScript and JavaScript examples for the 'before' and 'after' states.

```tsx
import Head from 'next/head'

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <>
      <Head>
        <title>My page title</title>
      </Head>
    </>
  )
}
```

